# Intuition
DFS and max between left and right subtree.

# Approach
Use dfs and check max left and right subtree value then return max(current,left,right), and check max answer at each and every node.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)

- Space complexity: O(1)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:

    int ans = INT_MIN;
    int solve(TreeNode * root)
    {
        if(root==NULL)
            return 0;

        int left = solve(root->left);
        int right = solve(root->right);
        // calculate the max path 
        // considering current node as a part of the path
        int path = root->val;
        path = max(path,path+left);
        path = max(path,path+right);

        //store the ans
        ans = max(ans,path);

        // return max(current node, left subtree, right subtree);
        return max(root->val,root->val+max(left,right));        
    }

    int maxPathSum(TreeNode* root) {
        ans = root->val;
        solve(root);
        return ans;
    }
};
```

