Basic idea is as follows :
1. Collect the number and store it in a stack
2. Update sign variable when you get '+' or '-'
3. Recurse whenever you see '('
4. Return the value whenever you see ')'

Here we could have done without stack but I wanted to establish a common implementation for all the 3 Basic calculator implementation.

```
class Solution {

    int i;    
    public int calculate(String s) {
        i = 0;
        return recurse(s);
    }

    public int recurse(String s) {
        int sign = 1;
        Stack<Integer> st = new Stack<>();

        while (i < s.length()) {
            char ch = s.charAt(i);
            if (ch == ' ') {
                i++;
                continue;
            }
            else if (Character.isDigit(ch)) {
                int num = 0;
                while (i < s.length() && Character.isDigit(s.charAt(i))) {
                    num = num*10 + (s.charAt(i) - '0');
                    i++;
                }
                st.push((sign*num));
            }
            else if (ch == '+' || ch == '-') {
                sign = (ch == '+') ? 1 : -1;
                i++;
            }
            else if (ch == '(') {
                i++;
                int num = recurse(s);
                st.push(sign*num);
            } 
            else if (ch == ')') {
                i++;
                break;
            }
        }

        int res = 0;
        while (!st.isEmpty()) {
            res += st.pop();
        }
        return res;

    }

}
```

