**This post is mainly for O(n) time and O(1) space complexity solution approach**.

So basically according to question we have sort first all even index with the values in decreasing order then secondly sort all odd index with the remaining values in decreasing order.

So this is basically consists of Three way partition(for sorting) with Virtual index(for sorting of desired index).
we have to apply three way partition in virtual indexes.

* For Three Way Partition refer to Sort colors ques of leetcode.
* For Virtual Indexing use-:
                  #define A(i) nums[(1+2*(i)) % (n|1)]     (used for macros)


After Virtual indexing we can access -:
for n = 10,
Accessing A(0) actually accesses nums[1].
Accessing A(1) actually accesses nums[3].
Accessing A(2) actually accesses nums[5].
Accessing A(3) actually accesses nums[7].
Accessing A(4) actually accesses nums[9].
Accessing A(5) actually accesses nums[0].
Accessing A(6) actually accesses nums[2].
Accessing A(7) actually accesses nums[4].
Accessing A(8) actually accesses nums[6].
Accessing A(9) actually accesses nums[8].

