1. First lets sort the array and instantiate a target array
1. We iterate from the back of the sorted array and fill up the target array starting from index=1.
1. In the target array, we jump index by 2 in each iteration. On reaching the end of the target array, we reset index back to 0.

Let's say the sorted array is like this [a b c d e f] and target is [. . . . . .]
Here's how we fill it
[. f . . . .]
[. f . e . .]
[. f . e . d]
[c f . e . d]
[c f b e . d]
[c f b e a d]

Since the initial array is sorted, we are assured that [c < f > b < e > a < d]
