# Intuition

<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
we can see a pattern like if the array is sorted in decending order than starting to mid will be placed in odd index and mid+1 to n will be at even index. This can only possible if array is sorted in decending order.

# Approach 
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Sort the array in decending order and start to mid will be at odd index and mid+1 to n will be at even. 
ex:---------------1,3,2,2,3,1
after sorting---  : 3 3 2 2 1 1 
mid+1 to n nos : 2 1 1
start to mid-----: 3 3 2

output-----------: **2 3 1 3 1 2**


