 Fill the <b>odd</b> indices (startig from 1)  with values in descending order.
 After that start filling the  <b>even</b> indices (starting  from 0 ) with next set of remaining  values! 
# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
     O(n)
- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
     O(n)
# Code
```
void wiggleSort(int* nums, int numsSize){
      int arr[5001];
      for(int i=0;i<5001;i++) arr[i]=0;
      for(int i=0;i<numsSize;i++){
          arr[nums[i]]++;
      }
      int end=5000;
      int in=1;   //start to  fill largest value from 1 index
       while(in<numsSize && end>-1){
          if(arr[end]==0){ end--; continue;}
          else{  nums[in]=end;
                 in+=2;
                 arr[end]--;
          }
      }
      in=0; // start to fill next set of values from index 0
        while(in<numsSize && end>-1){
          if(arr[end]==0){ end--; continue;}
          else{  nums[in]=end;
                 in+=2;
                 arr[end]--;
          }
      }
}
```

