Logic : 
a) Sliding Window : left and right pointer will be at the same position
								in favourable condition we increase the size of window i,e right++
								else
								we decrease the size of window i,e left++
	b) The condition here is: No. of Replacements should be less than or equal to k , per window
		No. of Replacements can be found by 
		length of window - maximum frequency of the character in the window
	i,e( (right- left +1) - maxf )  this value should be less than or equal to k
	if so we increase right [increasing size of window]
	else we increase left  [decreaseing size of window]
	c) simple by hand array hashing is used to maintain the frequency of elements 

	Time Complexity : O( n *26) which is O(n)
	Space Complexity is O(1) , as only constant space of 26 integer bytes is needed

