solutions.content:
Algorithm - Basic idea is to get the maximum frequency of the character in the window (using left and right pointers/references)

1) Create an array of size 26. As we know in question it defined that string consist of only UPPERCASE English characters.
2) Define a start and walker pointers, initialize both to 0. At the start of the algorithm both will point to same character.
3) Increment the walker and calculate the max frequnency of the window formed by start and walker. 
	3.1) If difference between window length ( `walker - start + 1` (adding 1 to get the length take an example and you will get it))  and the max frequency (`maxcount`) is greater than `k` (allowed number of replacement) then that means we have reached a position where we will not able to replace character within allowed number of replacement. We have to change the window by doing below 
				`cache[arr[start]-'A'] = cache[arr[start]-'A'] - 1;`
                `start++;`
	As we have moved the start pointer/reference we have to decrease the frequency of that particular character from our cache.
	3.2) if the difference is not greater than `k` that means we can still replace the charater so will calulate the max for the result.

The idea is not to actualy find which character to replace it's just to find the length of substring. This is the key to understand the problem and get the solution

Also the reason we are subtracting with ‘A’ is so that we can map English letter to array index 0-25 as char ‘A’ -‘A’ will give 0, ‘B’ - ‘A’ will give 1 likewise.

```
class Solution {
    public int characterReplacement(String s, int k) {

        int n = s.length();
        int[] cache = new int[26];
        int start = 0, maxcount = 0, res = 0;
        char[] arr = s.toCharArray();
        for(int walker=0; walker<n;walker++) {
            cache[arr[walker] - 'A'] =  cache[arr[walker] - 'A'] + 1;
            maxcount = Math.max(maxcount, cache[arr[walker]-'A']);
            if(walker - start + 1 - maxcount > k) {
                cache[arr[start]-'A'] = cache[arr[start]-'A'] - 1;
                start++;
            } else {
                res = Math.max(res, walker - start + 1);
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
}
```

