class Solution {
    public int characterReplacement(String s, int k) {
        int left = 0 , n = s.length();
        char[] sArray = s.toCharArray();
        int maxRepeatCharCount = 0;
        int[] count = new int[26];
        int longest = 0;

        for(int right = 0; right < n; right++) {
            char ch = sArray[right];
            count[ch-'A']++;
            maxRepeatCharCount = Math.max(maxRepeatCharCount, count[ch-'A']);
            int windowSize = right - left + 1;
            int replaceCount = windowSize - maxRepeatCharCount;
            while(replaceCount > k){
                count[sArray[left]-'A']--;
                left++;
                replaceCount--;
            }
            if(right-left + 1 > longest) {
                longest = right-left + 1;
            }
        }
        return longest;
    }
}

// Q: Why we don't update maxRepeatCharCount while shrinking the window?
// A: We can, but it won't effect the result longest = right - left + 1. Here's why:

// longest is recorded while this inequation stays true: windowSize - maxRepeatCharCount <= k
// Let's say the we record longest = 6, with the inequation being 6 - 4 <= 2
// during sliding window we expand the window and say it becomes 7, then there are 3 possibilities:

// maxRepeatCharCount decreases:
// 7 - 3 <= 2 => false

// maxRepeatCharCount stays the same:
// 7 - 4 <= 2 => false

// maxRepeatCharCount increases:
// 7 - 5 <= 2 => true

// this means the only case when we can get a longer window is when maxRepeatCharCount also increases alongside. 
// If maxRepeatCharCount doesn't increase, the line Math.max(longest, right - left + 1) will not update longest. 
// Therefore, there's no value in updating maxRepeatCharCount when its not increasing.
// If this still doesn't make sense, then feel free to always update maxRepeatCharCount and store all counts of all chars in a max heap.
//Retrieve the top of the heap everytime its required. Alternatively you can scan the frequency map linearly to find the max, but that'd be less efficient.
